Conservation status. The conservation status of
P. jeanneli
from Mt Kenya is assessed as least concern (LC) because it has an extent of occurrence and area of occupancy that are both in excess of the thresholds for vulnerability (VU) and there are no known widespread threats ( IUCN 2004 ;
Cumberlidge et al. 2009
). Its population is estimated to be stable based on indirect measures such as its representation in museum collections, although it was most recently collected back in 1962
